  "local_port": 58828,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which phone should I buy under INR 15K?",
  "response": "Choosing the right smartphone under \u20b915,000 in India involves balancing features like performance, camera quality, battery life, and display. As of October 2023, several excellent options offer great value within this budget. Here are some of the top contenders you might consider:\n\n### 1. **Poco X5 Pro**\n- **Display:** 6.67-inch Full HD+ AMOLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 778G\n- **RAM/Storage:** 6GB/128GB or 8GB/256GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** Triple camera setup \u2013 108MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n  - **Front:** 16MP\n- **Battery:** 5000mAh with 67W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** 5G support, MIUI based on Android 13\n\n### 2. **Realme 11 Pro+**\n- **Display:** 6.7-inch AMOLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** MediaTek Dimensity 7050\n- **RAM/Storage:** 6GB/128GB or 8GB/256GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** Triple camera \u2013 50MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n  - **Front:** 16MP\n- **Battery:** 5000mAh with 67W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** In-display fingerprint sensor, Realme UI based on Android 13\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M54**\n- **Display:** 6.7-inch Super AMOLED+, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Exynos 1380\n- **RAM/Storage:** 6GB/128GB or 8GB/256GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** Triple camera \u2013 50MP main, 12MP ultra-wide, 5MP macro\n  - **Front:** 32MP\n- **Battery:** 6000mAh with 25W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** One UI based on Android 13, expandable storage\n\n### 4. **Redmi Note 12 Pro+**\n- **Display:** 6.67-inch AMOLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 778G\n- **RAM/Storage:** 6GB/128GB or 8GB/256GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** 200MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n  - **Front:** 16MP\n- **Battery:** 5000mAh with 67W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** 5G support, MIUI based on Android 13\n\n### 5. **Motorola Edge 40 Neo**\n- **Display:** 6.55-inch OLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** MediaTek Dimensity 8020\n- **RAM/Storage:** 8GB/128GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** Triple camera \u2013 50MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n  - **Front:** 16MP\n- **Battery:** 4700mAh with 100W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** Clean Android experience, 5G support\n\n### 6. **OnePlus Nord CE 3 Lite**\n- **Display:** 6.72-inch LCD, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 695\n- **RAM/Storage:** 6GB/128GB or 8GB/256GB\n- **Camera:**\n  - **Rear:** Triple camera \u2013 64MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n  - **Front:** 16MP\n- **Battery:** 5000mAh with 67W fast charging\n- **Other Features:** OxygenOS based on Android 13, 5G support\n\n### **Key Considerations When Choosing:**\n\n1. **Performance:** If you\u2019re into gaming or multitasking, prioritize phones with higher RAM and a robust processor like the Snapdragon 778G or MediaTek Dimensity series.\n\n2. **Camera Quality:** For photography enthusiasts, look for higher megapixel counts and versatile camera setups. Phones like the Redmi Note 12 Pro+ with a 200MP sensor stand out.\n\n3. **Display:** AMOLED screens offer better colors and contrast compared to LCDs. Additionally, a higher refresh rate (120Hz) ensures smoother visuals.\n\n4. **Battery Life:** A larger battery (5000mAh or more) with fast charging support ensures longer usage and quick recharges.\n\n5. **Software Experience:** Consider the user interface and update promises. Brands like Samsung and Motorola offer reliable software support.\n\n6. **5G Support:** Future-proof your purchase by opting for a 5G-capable device, ensuring faster internet speeds as networks expand.\n\n### **Final Thoughts**\n\nYour ideal smartphone depends on your specific needs and preferences. If camera quality and performance are top priorities, the **Poco X5 Pro** or **Redmi Note 12 Pro+** are excellent choices. For a balanced experience with a clean software interface, the **Motorola Edge 40 Neo** or **OnePlus Nord CE 3 Lite** might be more suitable. Always check the latest prices and user reviews before making a decision, as offers and availability can change frequently.",
